itec.minicompiler.SymbolTable
Class StructuralSymbol

java.lang.Object
  itec.minicompiler.SymbolTable.Symbol
      itec.minicompiler.SymbolTable.StructuralSymbol
public class StructuralSymbol
extends Symbol

The StructuralSymbol implements a Symbol in the SymbolTable which is used to build the structure of the SymbolTable.

A StructuralSymbol can be of one of three types:

  • UNIVERSE (The top-scope and the root of the SymbolTable)
  • MODULE (The top-scope of all user-specific Symbols)
  • HEAD (The first Symbol in the local scope of any Symbol)
